==Anglo-Saxon==
===Verb===
'''bádian'''

# to take a pledge or fine

===Pronunciation===
*ba:·di·an

===Declension===
====Present Tense====
=====Indicative=====
*Singular: ic bádie, þu bádast, hé bádaþ
*plural: wé, gé, híe bádiaþ
=====Subjunctive=====
*Singular: bádie
*plural: bádien
=====Imperative=====
*Singular: báda!
*plural: bádiaþ!
=====Participle=====
*bádiende
====Past Tense====
=====Indicative=====
*Singular: ic bádode, þu bádodest, hé bádode
*plural: wé, gé, híe bádodon
=====Subjunctive=====
*Singular: bádode
*plural: bádoden
=====Participle=====
*gebádod
====Inflected Infinitive====
*tó bádienne

===Etymology===
*Derived from [[bád]] {{f}}, ''forced contribution, impost, pledge''; ''expectation''; itself derived from the past tense singular stem (bád) of [[bídan]].

===Derived terms===
*''Nouns'': [[bádiend]] {{m}}